Important Points About Using export DJANGO_SETTINGS_MODULE
In powershell, you can set the DJANGO_SETTINGS_MODULE environment variable using the following command:
$env:DJANGO_ENV = "production"
$env:DJANGO_ENV = "development"

in powershell:
cd "C:\Users\Kompiuteris\Downloads\Django 3- Resources\storefront3"
.\env\Scripts\Activate
$env:DJANGO_ENV = "development"
$env:DJANGO_ENV = "production"
echo $env:DJANGO_ENV
python manage.py runserver

In cmd:
cd "C:\Users\Kompiuteris\Downloads\Django 3- Resources\storefront3"
env\Scripts\Activate
set DJANGO_ENV=development
set DJANGO_ENV=production
echo %DJANGO_ENV%
python manage.py runserver


On Your Linux Server for Production: Set DJANGO_ENV=production:
export DJANGO_ENV=production then run the server
Alternatively, you can set the DJANGO_ENV in your .env files or use a system-level configuration like Supervisor or systemd for production.
